Preprocessing

  • This dataset contains set of traffic announcements entered into the system by the Transport Management Center operators from from 2018 to 2020 which are stored in 2 different datasets.
  • There are 12 variables, with using Rbind 58,422 observations is obtained.
  • We converted Turkish variable and record names into English words.
  • We transformed Announcement Types and Accident Types variables into factorized variables.
  • We filtered out some observations, where we did some calculations, in 2020 dataset because of the change in date and time structure but kept them in time series operations where we just did counting.

Relationship Between the 2019 Election and Running Projects

  • First round of the election March 2019
  • Second round of the election June 2019
  • Filtered announcement types are;Landscaping,Maintenance,Infrastructure Work,Construction Work-Structure,Construction Work-Road.

Effect of the Pandemic on the Number of Accidents

  • The first pandemic case occurred in March in Turkey.

  • In April and May, there were a lot of lockdowns were applied.

Effect of the Pandemic on the Number of Accidents

  • 15th of July is a national holiday in Turkey.

Distribution of the Announcement Types During Holidays

Holiday event calendar is introduced to the dataset.

During Holiday;

  • Accident and vehicle breakdown reasons are the majority of announcements.

  • Municipality may prefer to work on maintenance works.

Conclusion

  • According to our problem index, infrastructure work & construction work-road are the worst traffic makers.

  • Maintenance & Accident Notification are occur more frequently so in total, these are the worst for traffic.

  • Considering that there will be an election in March 2019, the number of projects carried out compared to the last quarter of the previous year has increased.

  • With the new administration and the elimination of election uncertainty, the number of projects carried out by the municipality has started to increase regularly from the last quarter of 2019.

  • The number of accidents significantly decreased during the pandemic.

  • After rule bendings the number of accidents are increased to the standard levels.

  • During holiday times, accident notifications & vehicle breakdown notifications compose about 80% of total notifications.
